Quarter Ending: For the quarters ending June 2007 to March 2010 all patients waiting over 26 weeks have been included in the '>26 week' timeband.
From the quarter ending June 2010, patients waiting over 26 weeks have been split into the timebands '>26 - 36 weeks' and '> 36 weeks'.
From the quarter ending June 2012, patients waiting over 26 weeks have been split into the timebands '>26 - 30 weeks', '>30-36 weeks' and '> 36 weeks'.
From the quarter ending June 2013, patients waiting over 26 weeks have been split into the timebands '>26 - 30 weeks', '>30 weeks'.
From the quarter ending June 2014, patients waiting greater than 26 weeks have been included in the ' > 26 weeks timeband'
It has not been possible to accurately split the number of inpatients waiting in the >26-36 and >36 week timebands in the Urology, T & O Surgery
and Pain Management specialties at the Belfast HSC Trust at 31st March 2012.  The overall number of inpatients waiting in these timebands have
been adjusted on the basis of the total proportion of day cases and ordinary admissions waiting at Belfast HSC Trust at 31st March 2012.
